dvertently producing h...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.27375", "source": "arXiv NLP", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.27375v1/2605.27375v1/x1.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2605.28064v1", "title": "I Hear, Therefore I Trust: A Socio-Technical Investigation of Humans as Synthetic Speech Detectors", "summary": "Abstract: Automatic deepfake detection has received considerable research attention, yet the socio-technical environment in which humans actually encounter synthetic speech remains poorly understood. We investigate voice deepfake detection as a perceptual and contextual process, presenting a localiz...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.28064", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.28064v1/2605.28064v1/imgs/fig_markers.png", "score": 10}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2605.28480v1", "title": "Audio-Mind: An Auditable Agentic Framework for Audio Understanding", "summary": "Abstract: Audio agents extend large audio-language models (LALMs) by decomposing audio questions into tool calls, intermediate evidence, and iterative reasoning steps. However, as LALMs become stronger, the key challenge shifts from enabling tool use to determining when agentic evidence acquisition ...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.28480", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.28480v1/2605.28480v1/x1.png", "score": 10}]}